meaningMnemonic: You have the <kanji>ordinal number prefix</kanji> and 一位 (first place). By adding the prefix 第, you can make it a little more formal, but it still means <vocabulary>first place</vocabulary>.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
